         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e5931"> </a>Remove the LH switch (3): disconnect connector from main wiring and loosen screws (4).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_014803481.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="titoleto"><a name="d3e5936"> </a>Removing the handgrips
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e5938"> </a>Loosen internal screw and remove plug (5) to remove handgrips (6).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e5940"> </a>Slide out handgrips (6) making sure not to damage them.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_008403482.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="titoleto"><a name="d3e5945"> </a>Removing the handlebar
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e5947"> </a>Undo and remove the screws (7) securing the U-bolt (8).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e5949"> </a>Remove the U-bolt (8).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e5951"> </a>Remove the handlebar (9) from its seat on the steering head.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_014903493.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e5956"> </a>Loosen the screws (10), and remove the stud bolts (11) from the steering head; recover the washers (12).
         </div>
      </div>
